ADPresident Trump and Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin are seeking the extra small-business money after banks fielded more than 400,000 loan requests in less than a week for firms trying to navigate the economic fallout from the coronavirus pandemic.
Many Democrats have also supported the small-business initiative, called the Paycheck Protection Program at the Small Business Administration.
On a conference call with House Democrats on Wednesday Pelosi and Majority Leader Steny H. Hoyer (D-Md.)
AD“I want to assure all small businesses out there we will not run out of money,” Mnuchin said.
A number of small businesses have complained that the application process is confusing and difficult to navigate.